<p>The main problem I am having is getting a user input for a simple Sequential Search algorithm.</p>  <p>By the searchName string, I put it as "JOptionPane.showInputDialog("Input Name")", Whenever I put this and input correct names, it always returns False.</p>  <p>But when I just replace the JOptionPane with a string, it will be true, unless the array doesn't contain the string.</p>  <p>My question is, how can I make the user input work? Thanks in advance for the responses. </p>  <pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {     // TODO Auto-generated method stub       String[] names = {"Ada", "Ben", "Carol", "Dave", "Ed", "Frank", "Gerri", "Helen", "Iggy", "Joan"};      boolean result;      String searchName = JOptionPane.showInputDialog("Input Name");      int size = names.length;      result = sequentialSearch(names, searchName, size);           if (result == true){         System.out.println("The name " + searchName + " was found.");     }     else{         System.out.println("The name " + searchName + " was not found.");     }  }  public static boolean sequentialSearch(String[] anarray, String t, int n){     /*      * n is the amount of space in the array, t is the name you are looking for.      */       boolean found =false;      for(int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++){         if(anarray[i] == t){             found = true;         }      }     return found;    } </code></pre>  <p>}</p>